$interpreted: : Some Time Later...
Tingko: Hey, that's is my job!
Jihasaha: Well it's the middle of the night and you're still not done! Step aside.

Jiyanama: You two argue about the littlest of things. 
What children...
Tingko: Jiyanama, I don't want to argue, but he keeps annoying me! Plus, he's always bothering the princess...
Tindoiimu: Tingko, stop worrying. He just cares about me. This is just how Jihasaha is. Maybe you should spend some time getting to know him.
Tingko: Alright, I'll try... but, only because the princess said so.
Jihasaha: Princess, I have a request.
Tindoiimu: You want Tingko to leave, right? Yeah, you've brought it up before...
Jihasaha: She's useless! She just hangs around and makes things worse!
Tindoiimu: You have to stop antagonizing her, Jihasaha. Why don't you try and make a new friend?
Jihasaha: ...Okay, I will try. For you, princess.
: Six Months Later...
Jihasaha: (I wonder what that kid'll yell at me for this time. Last time it was my tone, and before that it was the way I ate...)
Jihasaha: (So annoying, I shouldn't have to think about this nonsense. That's it, I'm insisting the princess get rid of her this time.)
Jihasaha: Whoever it is, come on out! Or just hide and embarass yourself, makes no difference to me.
???: Whelp, guess you caught me.
Alert Guard: You still remember me, punk?
Alert Guard: You sucker-punched me once when I was drunk. Don't say you don't remember.
Jihasaha: Don't remember. Don't care.
Alert Guard: Arrogant little...
Alert Guard: Listen, you've got two choices. One, get on your knees and apologize. Two, leave here in a body bag.
Jihasaha: And I'll give you two choices. One, run home with your tail between your legs...

Jihasaha: And two... 
Actually, forget it. I know which one you'll pick.
Alert Guard: Punk! You're dead!
Tingko: Hey princess, is Jihasaha late?
Tindoiimu: He is a bit later than usual... Think he ran into some trouble?
Tindoiimu: Jihasaha! You're late! You're usually right on time...
Jihasaha: Ran into some thugs on the road trying to start something. It's nothing.
Tindoiimu: You're okay?
Jihasaha: Don't worry, princess. 'Tis but a scratch.
Tingko: (Why does he seem so calm, today?)
Jihasaha: I have some military duties to attend to. Please excuse me.

Tingko: Princess, did he seem weird to you? 
His tone is usually way more... arrogant?
Tindoiimu: Very perceptive.
Tingko: Don't make fun of me! I'm serious. I've known him for a bit now, it's hard not to notice.
Tindoiimu: I'm actually a bit worried about him, too. Tingko, could you...
Jihasaha: This should be far enough—ugh!
Jihasaha: (Never thought I would get so hurt. I'm still too weak.)
Jihasaha: (I can't let the princess see me like this... And especially not that little brat...)
Manly Guard: There you are.
Jihasaha: (Agh, there's more of them...)
Manly Guard: What's wrong? Oh no~ Got a little boo-boo?
Manly Guard: You were so tough before. Now let's see if you've got any fight left in you!
Jihasaha: (Princess, forgive me. I've let you down...)
Manly Guard: Agh!
Jihasaha: (...Who is it...? What a... warm... light...)
